Dikembe Mutombo was elected to the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame on Monday . 
  Mutombo played in the NBA from 1991 until 2009 . 
  He was an eight-times NBA All-Star famous for swatting away shots and wagging his finger at opponents . 
  The Congolese centre was a four-time NBA Defensive Player of the Year . 
 